  "description": "A sprout is a germinated seed harvested and eaten before true leaves develop, typically within three to seven days of soaking. In [home gardening](../index.md), sprouts are among the simplest crops to grow because they require no soil, no light (in most cases), and no specialized equipment beyond a jar and clean water.",
